news.title: Tamil Nadu registration department installs fingerprint scanners to combat fraud
news.para: All 582 sub-registrar offices in the state now have fingerprint scanner facilities, and the buyer-seller’s biometrics will be matched against the one-crore-plus sample data bank they have.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh CM visits Amaravati, promises white paper on the capital city
news.para: ​Amaravati capital city project came to a standstill for five-long years from 2019 to 2024 under the YS Jagan Mohan Reddy-led YSRCP government. However, the change in government breathed life into the capital city project.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body cancels allotment of eight Indirapuram plots
news.para: The allotment, which took place in 2003, was carried out under the supervision of the then development authority secretary, Shyam Singh Yadav.

news.title: About 65% of survey of dangerous buildings complete: Delhi civic body
news.para: According to MCD officials, the action was taken after issuing prior notices and providing adequate time to the owners or occupiers to demolish the buildings for safety reasons.

news.title: Government approves Rs 2,870 crore development plan for Varanasi airport
news.para: ​The Lal Bahadur Shastri International Airport at Varanasi, the Lok Sabha constituency of Prime Minister Narendra Modi, can currently handle 3.3 million passengers per annum.

news.title: Property registrations in Maharashtra rise amid unchanged RR rates
news.para: The state recorded 3.35 lakh property registrations and clocked Rs 3,767.12 crore revenue in April this year as compared to 3.34 lakh registrations and Rs 2,876.40 crore income in the same period last year.

news.title: Dharavi redevelopment project seeks 15 acres of land in BKC from MMRDA on lease for five years
news.para: According to sources, DRPPL intends to use this BKC land, previously a Metro works casting yard, for storing heavy machinery necessary for Dharavi's redevelopment.

news.title: Awfis posts Rs 1.3 crore profit in in Q4 FY24
news.para: In the March quarter, total expenses rose YoY to Rs 239.7 crore from Rs 178.7 crore. A significant amount of the expenditure was attributed to subcontracting costs and other expenses.

news.title: Nisus Finance invests Rs 155 crore in affordable housing project in Surat
news.para: The project is part of a larger layout on a 12-acre land parcel comprising 4.5 million sq ft. The first phase of the ongoing project comprises 21 towers with 1.3 million sq ft of saleable area.

news.title: UK’s Berkeley plans to start a build-to-rent platform
news.para: Investors were largely unmoved by the slight increase in guidance for the current financial year, although this may reflect a recent strong run for the shares and also the modest drop in margins and profit reported for the full year

news.title: General Atlantic, Asia Opportunities V to sell 4% stake worth Rs 830 crore in PNB Housing Finance
news.para: General Atlantic is expected to sell shares worth Rs 420 crore, while Asia Opportunities V (Mauritius) will sell shares worth Rs 410 crore.

news.title: Oakley's founder sells his Malibu home for $210 million
news.para: The uber-luxury pad -- which is a lot of money even by the jaw-dropping standards of Malibu's expensive real estate -- is now the costliest home ever to be sold in California.

news.title: Enforcement directorate files second prosecution complaint in Shine City fraud case
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) has filed a prosecution complaint in a Rs 1,000 crore alleged money laundering case against real estate firm Shine City, whose owner and officials have been booked by police in over 550 FIRs lodged across Uttar Pradesh, the agency said on Wednesday.

news.title: Over 1,200 illegal structures razed in Lucknow’s Akbarnagar
news.para: Over 1,320 illegal structures, including the religious places of both Hindu and Muslim communities, have been demolished in the area, the LDA officials said that around 100 buildings were demolished on Tuesday and added the work of clearing the debris will be undertaken now.

news.title: Visakhapatnam awaits big development push from new government
news.para: Aside from completing the NAD flyover project, the city has yet to see any new flyovers to alleviate traffic congestion. The Bhogapuram international airport stands out as the major project that has been launched and is currently progressing.

news.title: Greater Noida authority rolls out development plan worth Rs 73 crore
news.para: In addition to the road resurfacing, the development plan includes the installation of LED lights in village plots, worth Rs 6.85 crore, aimed at improving safety and visibility in several villages.

news.title: Government making efforts to develop Hyderabad as one of world's best cities: Telangana CM
news.para: The chief minister said that the number of people staying in America from Telangana and the number of people who have returned from USA is increasing Hence, Hyderabad should be developed on par with New York City, the CM said.

news.title: Builders in Jharkhand grapple with skyrocketing sand prices
news.para: Vikash Vijayvargia, a city-based contractor who builds overhead water tanks for state govt in the city and across the district, claimed that sand shortage have forced work to come to a halt for nearly four months now.
